cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.NA, cs.CV 

The paper discusses optimization theory for minimizing smooth strongly convex finite sums, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of sampling without replacement, which is a common technique in data structures and algorithms, suggesting possible categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The mention of theoretical convergence rates suggests a possible category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and the mention of empirical results suggests a possible category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
